      <h2>Program Overview</h2>

      <p>This 8-week intermediate dead hang program builds a 60-90 second hold through four weekly sessions. Grip variety drives progress at this stage. Overhand, underhand, and neutral grips rotate across sessions to stress every forearm muscle.</p>

      <p>The program introduces <a href="/passive-vs-active-hang/">active hangs</a> in the final phase. Active hangs engage the scapular muscles during the hold. This combination of passive and active work builds both raw grip endurance and shoulder stability.</p>

